This article discusses the tragic shooting that took place at Marjory Stoneman Douglas High School in Parkland, Florida, on February 14th, 2018. It highlights the devastating impact of the shooting on the Parkland community and the country as a whole. The article mentions the efforts of the Parkland families and the broader American community in advocating for stricter gun control measures. The author mentions a comprehensive plan put forward by the administration to reduce gun violence, including measures such as curbing the proliferation of "ghost" guns, cracking down on violators of gun laws, promoting safe firearm storage, and supporting law enforcement models that remove shooters from the streets. The article concludes by calling on Congress to take further action, such as implementing universal background checks, banning assault weapons and high-capacity magazines, and eliminating immunity for gun manufacturers.